The paper describes a system for automatic news category and keyphrase labeling, which involves training a neural network on a large dataset of news articles and using various methods for keyphrase extraction. This work involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques, which are commonly associated with the CS.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Additionally, the use of neural networks and machine learning algorithms suggests a connection to the CS.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and CS.LG (Learning) sub-categories. The use of statistical, graphical, and numerical methods for keyphrase extraction suggests a connection to the CS.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Finally, the use of pre-identified category labels and the focus on improving the speed at which users can find relevant content suggests a connection to the CS.DL (Deep Learning) sub-category.
